BLACK MESA LOBBY, MUSEUM


Sam, we've been dumped right into the sterile cold of Black Mesa. Into a quiet corner of the complex, where respectable people in white coats once gave tours and told us about the advances of science. Now it smells of blood, sweat, and madness. A different kind of madness. Not ours.

The display cases contain cyclers. Creatures who, in life, could choose only one body. One scientist. One Vortigaunt. One soldier. And be frozen in it forever. They don't transform. They just... do the same thing. Over and over. Stand in the same pose. Stare at the same spot.

Black Mesa took advantage of this. Captured the cyclers, stuffed them into display cases, and put them on display. Look, kids, there's an alien. There's a soldier. There's a scientist who's always adjusting his glasses. They're not alive. But they're not dead either. They're an endless recording, frozen in glass.

When they're hit, they suddenly shift position. Then they freeze again. I don't know if they feel pain. Probably not. Or maybe they do. But what difference does it make? They're not people anymore. Not Vortigaunts. Not soldiers. They're exhibits. And Black Mesa is proud of its collection.

The museum exit leads to a lobby. A real lobby, with columns and a reception area. It's not quiet there now. There, security is battling Mental's horde. Shots, screams, plasma melting marble. Scientists who didn't have time to hide huddle against the walls. Some are crying. Some are praying. Some are simply staring into space-like those cyclers behind the glass.

And those who know are terrified. Because buried beneath the complex, deep in the silos, is a missile. And it could explode at any moment. The important thing is that if it explodes, Black Mesa will be gone. Along with us, the security, Mental, and the Cyclers, who won't even realize they're dead.

We can't solve anything in the museum. We need to get out to the lobby, sort out the chaos, find someone who knows how to defuse the missile. Or at least how to get out of the blast zone. Because if it explodes, neither the Buzzsaw nor your luck will help us.
